-Weary Tired Cookies:
-Base Ingredients
455 g all-purpose flour
216 g granulated sugar
66 g light brown sugar
7 tbsp unsalted butter
-Flavor Ingredients
200 g chocolate
2.0 tsp vanilla
2.0 tsp peppermint
---
Instructions
Step 1: Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F.
Step 2: Mix together dry ingredients, combining flour, ,  in a large bowl. In another bowl, cream together granulated sugar, light brown sugar and  unsalted butter, then add vanilla, peppermint.
Step 3: Gradually add the dry ingredients to the wet ingredients, mixing well. Once mixed, add the chocolate.
Step 4: Let the mixture rest for 4 hours in the refrigerator. On a baking sheet lined with parchment paper, add 40 grams of dough, rolled into a sphere. Bake for 12 minutes, turning the sheet around halfway through the baking time. 
Step 5: Let the cookies cool.